DOM(Document Object Model)
	It is used in web development used to interact and manipulate(change) the html documents.
	When the web page is loaded, the browser creates DOM of the webpage.
	When the html file is loaded into the browser, the javascript directly cannot understand the html document.
	DOM : it is basically the representation of same html document but in a tree like structure composed of objects.
KEY POINTS:
a.	Structure : The DOM represents the structure of HTML document as tree. Each   node in tree represents the elements , an attribute or text.
b.	Manipulation : using javascript, you can interact with elements(buttons, paragraphs) on the webpage, changing the content, styles , can add or remove elements.
c.	Event handing: you can handle the interactions, like click or pressing the button
d.	W3C(world wide web consortium)

Methods of Document Objects:
--Used to interact with and manipulate the document
Getting Element:
a.	Getting element by id
b.	Getting element by class
c.	Getting element by tag
d.	Getting an element by query selector
